            <h2>A Brief History of Coffee</h2>
            <p>Coffee is believed to have originated in Ethiopia, with its cultivation and trade beginning on the Arabian Peninsula. By the 15th century, it was being grown in the Yemeni district of Arabia and by the 16th century, it was known in Persia, Egypt, Syria, and Turkey.</p>
